version: 1
display_name: PHTN-50-000039 - The operating system must store only encrypted representations of passwords.
global_description: |-
  Passwords need to be protected at all times, and encryption is the standard method for protecting passwords. If passwords are not encrypted, they can be plainly read (i.e., clear text) and easily compromised.
osfinger:
  - VMware Photon OS-5
refs:
  disa_stig:
    - PHTN-50-000039
  srg:
    - SRG-OS-000073-GPOS-00041
  cci:
    - CCI-004062
  nist:
    - IA-5 (1) (d)
benchmark_id:
  vcf9_photon_5:
    type: custom
    desc: The operating system must store only encrypted representations of passwords.
    control_id: PHTN-50-000039
    scored: true
    profile:
      - default
    information: |-
      At the command line, run the following command to verify passwords are stored with only encrypted representations:

      # grep ^ENCRYPT_METHOD /etc/login.defs

      Example result:

      ENCRYPT_METHOD SHA512

      If the "ENCRYPT_METHOD" option is not set to "SHA512", is missing or commented out, this is a finding.
    rationale: |-
      Passwords need to be protected at all times, and encryption is the standard method for protecting passwords. If passwords are not encrypted, they can be plainly read (i.e., clear text) and easily compromised.
    remediation: |-
      Navigate to and open:

      /etc/login.defs

      Add or update the following line:

      ENCRYPT_METHOD SHA512
